[id="creating-a-custom-container-image-for-ray-clusters_{context}"]
= Creating a custom container image for Ray clusters

[role='_abstract']
Learn how to build and push a custom container image for Ray clusters to your registry, so that you can run distributed workloads in {productname-short}.

There are two options for creating a custom container image for Ray clusters: 

. Building custom ray container images using Podman

. Building custom ray container images using the integrated {productname-short} registry

[NOTE]
====
Any examples are provided for documentation purposes on how to build custom container images for distributed workloads. These examples are not supported by {openshift-platform} and are not a part of {productname-short}.
====

